				<div class="clear"></div>
				<div class="body">
					<p>Hi Felix,</p>
<p>It's probably worth mentioning that in 1.2, if you use arrays for your urls this gets a lot simpler</p>
<p>(ref: http://www.ad7six.com/MiBlog/MakingTheMostOfTheRouter)</p>
<p>Using this logic you can loop on a menu and in brief:</p>
<p>if $url['plugin'] == $this-&gt;plugin<br />
   Then you are in the same plugin*</br></p>
<p>if $url['controller'] == $this-&gt;name<br />
   Then you are in the same controller</br></p>
<p>if $url['action'] == $this-&gt;action<br />
   Then you are in the same function</br></p>
<p>This doesn't work without a minor change to the router, but I'll mention it anyway<br />
if $url == Router::url(array())</br><br />
  The link is to the page you are currently on</br></p>
<p>Even if you don't use arrays for your urls you can still make use of this by passing the url to the router to get the url back as an array to then test it.</p>
<p>hth,</p>
<p>AD<br />
*Plugin routes don't work atm unless you add a patch (see tickets)</br></p>
